# Vocello agent playbook

Repo facts and architecture live in [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md). This rule is the **execution layer**: which Axiom agents, skills, and MCPs to use when.

## Mandatory Axiom Task launches (high-risk)

Launch via `Task` with the listed `subagent_type` **before** deep code changes. After the audit, fix findings or explicitly defer them before claiming done.

| Trigger | `subagent_type` | Repo notes |
|---|---|---|
| Xcode/build/env failure | `build-fixer` | Run `./scripts/build.sh debug` first, then agent |
| `.ips` / MetricKit / crash paste | `crash-analyzer` | Engine XPC: `QwenVoiceEngineService` |
| Actor/async/engine gates (`MLXTTSEngine`, XPC hosts, iOS extension) | `concurrency-auditor` | Prewarm gate + generation ownership are CRITICAL |
| Memory policy / streaming / MLX cache / trim | `memory-auditor` | Pair with `swift-performance-analyzer` on same diff |
| GRDB migrations / schema changes | `database-schema-auditor` | macOS + iOS SharedSupport |
| Release / signing / entitlements / privacy manifest | `security-privacy-scanner` | Before TestFlight or macOS ship |
| User asks health check / full audit / scan everything | `health-check` | Orchestrates parallel auditors; `scratch/` if requested |

## Recommended Axiom launches (symptom / scope)

| Symptom or scope | `subagent_type` | Skill (read when present) |
|---|---|---|
| Slow / janky UI | `swiftui-performance-analyzer` | `axiom:axiom-swiftui` |
| Logic in views / testability | `swiftui-architecture-auditor` | same |
| Layout / iPad breakage | `swiftui-layout-auditor` | same |
| Navigation / deep links | `swiftui-nav-auditor` | same |
| Dead-end sheets / empty states | `ux-flow-auditor` | `axiom:axiom-accessibility` for a11y overlap |
| Liquid Glass / Reduce Transparency | `liquid-glass-auditor` | `axiom:axiom-audit-liquid-glass` |
| `@Observable` / legacy SwiftUI | `modernization-helper` | |
| Codable / JSON / contract drift | `codable-auditor` | |
| HF downloads / URLSession | `networking-auditor` | `hugging-face:hf-cli` for Hub ops |
| File paths / backup bloat | `storage-auditor` | |
| Battery / timers / polling | `energy-auditor` | |
| Headless profiling evidence | `performance-profiler` | `axiom:axiom-profile-performance` |
| SPM resolve / module errors | `spm-conflict-resolver` | |

Prioritize auditors marked **always** in [`scratch/health-check-2026-05-26.md`](../../scratch/health-check-2026-05-26.md): memory, concurrency, swift-performance, codable, security, modernization.

## MCP routing (Cursor)

| Need | Server | When |
|---|---|---|
| macOS Vocello UI smoke/bench | `user-computer-use` | [`docs/reference/computer-use-mcp.md`](../../docs/reference/computer-use-mcp.md) |
| Apple build / run / test | `user-xcodebuildmcp` | Prefer over raw `xcodebuild`; call `session_show_defaults` first |
| Library docs (MLX, GRDB, SwiftUI, Vite) | `user-context7` | User-level Context7 rule applies globally |
| Hugging Face Hub | `plugin-huggingface-skills-huggingface-skills` | Catalog, downloads, contract revisions |
| Marketing site only | Vercel / browser MCP | Not for native app UI |

**Forbidden:** `user-automation-mcp` for Vocello UI; osascript UI driving.

## Performance router

Slow / memory / leak / battery / RTF regression: read **`axiom:axiom-performance`** skill first, then pick profiler or auditor above. Engine regressions: `./scripts/uitest.sh bench-step` + `bench-compare` per [`docs/reference/computer-use-mcp.md`](../../docs/reference/computer-use-mcp.md).

## Repo scripts (authoritative)

| Task | Entry |
|---|---|
| macOS debug build | `./scripts/build.sh debug` or `run` |
| UI smoke / bench | `./scripts/uitest.sh` + `user-computer-use` |
| iOS compile-safety | `./scripts/build_foundation_targets.sh ios` |
| Real iPhone | `./scripts/ios_device.sh doctor` / `start` |
| macOS release | `./scripts/release.sh` |

Do not reintroduce CI test workflows or parallel harnesses without maintainer decision.
